ZCZC EE29
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
WEDNESDAY TO SATURDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 212300 UTC
ON WEDNESDAY EVENING LOW PRESSURE WILL BE MOV FM THE NORWEGIAN SEA AND
INTO SCANDINAVIA FLN IN THE PROCESS. ANOTHER AREA OF LOW PRESSURE WILL BE
POSITIONED CLOSE TO SERN IBERIA DURING THE PERIOD. MEANWHILE THE NITON SEA
AREAS WILL BE DOMINATED BY AN AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE 1032 EXTENDING FM MAINLAND
EUROPE ACROSS THE UK N SEA AND SERN SCANDINAVIA. HIGH PRESSURE CENTRE WILL
DRIFT SLWY WWARDS TO BECOME CENTRED OVER THE NW OF THE UK BY THE END OF SATURDAY.
LOW PRESSURE CENTRES WILL REMAIN TO THE N W AND S OF THE ANTICYCLONE AND
OUTSIDE OF UK SURROUNDING WATERS. NO HAZARDOUS WINDS ARE EXP ACROSS NITON
THROUGHOUT THIS PERIOD BUT ARE LIKELY TO BE STRG FOR A TIME ESPECIALLY ACROSS
FITZROY AND BISCAY ON WEDNESDAY EVENING AND POSSIBLY INTO THE FIRST HALF
OF THURSDAY AS THE LOW CENTRE NEAR IBERIA CLEARS S
